<br Among the first to congratulate the election, Meloni also expressed "satisfaction for the broad agreement reached between the parliamentary forces". Meet the leader dem: "The agreement has held with great compactness both of the opposition and of the majority. Very well, there is great satisfaction," says Schlein. For Tajani the election "is a good signal for democracy". An important controversy is the green Angelo Bonelli, who claims the "great sense of responsibility" demonstrated by the opposition, "a responsibility that we have not seen in the majority until the last". And that today's understanding is only a parentheses it also means the group leader of Chiara Braga (well the comparison but the political confrontation remains, it says in essence). For his part, FdI claims "the strong sense of responsibility, the seriousness and respect of the institutions of the district", say the two group leaders Galeazzo Bignami and Lucio Malan. And Count Chiosa: "At the end we had the clearest ideas of the majority forces that came to the last."

