AGI - Pasti based on bread and oil for children and girls of families back with the payments of the school canteen. It happens in Montevarchi, in the province of Arezzo, in the State Comprehensive Institute, "Raffaello Magiotti". A school that is "characterized by a high presence of families and students of different ethnic groups and cultures for which design has been strongly influenced", as read in the Institute website. The Institute Council, however, declines all responsibility and, indeed, it is said to be contrary to the measure with a document unanimously voted.' "The daughters and children of families who do not pay canteen are given only bread and oil. This while their companions and their companions eat a full meal", denounces the regional councillor of Tuscany Alessandra Nardini. "But does the mayor realize what this means to them?", question Nerdini.
&nbsp;
To lead the Municipality of Montevarchi is Silvia Chiassai Martini, mayor elected with the centerdestra>. "The Minister Valditara had spoken of humiliation as a factor of growth, evidently the mayor Chiassai took it just in the letter and therefore I turn to her asking that she return to this shameful choice," adds Nardini. The echo of what happens in Montevarchi reaches Rome causing a rose of shields from the centerleft in defense of children and girls who are eating a slice of bread and oil, "fettunta" in Tuscan>, next to the comrades who, instead, consume a full meal. "The mayor of Montevarchi, Silvia Chiassai Martini, imposes bread and oil to the children of morbid parents. It is a cruelty that generates ghettos, it is horrible, the competent authorities intervene to bring the reason back to the Tuscan commune," Luana Zanella, leader of Avs at the House.
&nbsp;
"What is happening in some schools in Montevarchi, in the province of Arezzo, is unacceptable from every point of view", underline in a joint note Marco Furfaro of the national secretariat Pd, the regional secretary Emiliano Fossi, the deputies Laura Boldrini and Marco Simiani of the Democratic Party: "There are children who in some schools of the municipality are forced to eat bread and oil only because families are sour towards the canteen service. A choice, by the municipal administration, which makes it shiver.> The mayor and the right administration who are leading this 'legal' crusade should only be ashamed. We are faced with an unjust practice and completely out of time that puts at risk the physical psycho health of children in the school environment which is the place where they should in any case and in every social situation find inclusion, welcome, well-being and solidarity. A civil country cannot accept that such measures apply to minors," the dems conclude.
&nbsp;
From the 5 Star Movement is the Tuscan Congressman Andrea Quartini to stigmatize the event: "A measure that knows about medieval punishment, a meschina choice that uses the little ones as a blackmail tool.> Because, if it really was a matter of moral rigor and justice, then bread and oil should eat it all the members of the League until their party returns the famous 49 million euros," says Quartini: "It should be eaten Augusta Montaruli, sentenced to peculate, who with public money paid personal expenses. And the whole party of Forza Italia should have lunch, founded by a convicted tax evasion. If there's someone who should go back to school to take lessons of civilization, that's the mayor of Montevarchi and the entire ruling class of the center-right that doesn't distance itself from mescan and ignoble actions like this to the detriment of children who have nothing to do with it." &nbsp;&nbsp;

