&nbsp;
"Nova Gorica and Gorizia love to celebrate the culture of borders. With Chemnitz, in Germany, Nova Gorica was chosen as the European capital of 2025 culture and the Slovenian city wanted to launch with the twin Gorizia a challenge: to propose itself as an experience of culture through the frontier", he adds.> "If culture, by definition, knows no boundaries, it is born, but always, as an expression of a community but open to knowledge, to common research, to mutual enrichment. The horrors of nationalist extremism, which has so badly produced in Europe - the head of the State notes - emerge the values of cohabitation and acceptance. These are the values that can oppose the obscurantism of war and conflict that has been reproposed with Russian aggression against Ukraine."
